
🛠️ JEANETTE Cybersecurity Framework: Operational Documentation

An integrated, multi-module Ruby command-line toolkit designed for security auditing, network reconnaissance, and host vulnerability assessment.
This manual provides the operational baseline, structural specifications, and dependency mapping required to execute and maintain the tool across approved platforms.
---

⚡ System Dependencies & SetupThe framework leverages native operating system terminal interfaces combined with specialized Ruby gems to manage ASCII decoration, platform checks, interactive prompts, and browser integration.

* artii → Responsible for parsing and generating block font ASCII typography.
* os → Executes environmental validation checks to verify system compatibility.
* readline → Powers the persistent interactive command prompt history buffer.
* launchy → Spawns default system browser threads to interface with web assets.


Initializing Environment Context:

📦 Core Architecture & Submenu Matrix
---
The framework decouples defensive tasks into dedicated sub-shells. Each operational branch utilizes independent variable scoping and custom prompt definitions (JEANETTE_NETWORKING>, JEANETTE_VULNERABILITY>).

1. Network Discovery ModuleGraphical Port Scanner Intercept: Calls internal scanner functions. Expects port_scanner.py to be staged locally in the active working directory with executable permissions (chmod +x).Wireless Network Environment Overview: Maps local radio space and interface states.Host Device Enumeration: Runs local asset discovery loops across the subnet.
2. Vulnerability Scanning ModuleVirusTotal Integration: Spawns a browser node directly to the global intelligence GUI via Launchy.Nessus Service Control: Executes a system service call (systemctl start nessusd.service) to spin up local scanner engines. Requires administrative/root authentication.CVE Lookups & Correlation: Matches system configurations against known threat dictionaries.
3. Social Engineering Detection Email Body Analyzer Identifier: Runs contextual triage loops on incoming message text.Credential Exposure Matrix: Audits databases for compromised account data.URL Reputation Integrity Check: Verifies web target safety vectors.
4. Configuration Auditing Privilege Escalation Mapping: Monitors access controls and permissions anomalies.User Account & Last Login Auditing: Inspects active system directories for credential tracking.NIST Standards Portal: Auto-launches the official regulatory baseline site for compliance review.
5. Decompiler for Malicious CodeGhidra Integration: Fires up reverse-engineering suites to break down binaries.Memory Dumps & Hex Modification: Captures volatile system storage blocks for binary auditing.


🛡️ Triage and Operation Verification
---

Standard Execution Flow:
1. The loader verifies platform compliance (Windows 10/11, Linux, MacOS).
2. The interactive shell loops continuously via a while Readline block.
3. Menus refresh dynamically; typing 6 in submenus triggers return_to_menu to cleanly clear local child arrays and re-sync the prompt state back to JEANETTE>.

Error Control Protocols:
* Nessus Fails to Boot: Ensure the service binary path maps to /bin/systemctl and your terminal holds sudo elevation before choosing the module.
* Browser Fails to Open via Launchy: Run sudo gem install launchy to re-sync missing system interface drivers.


🚀 Technical Performance Roadmap
---
* Hosting Control Repository: Core code updates, script additions, and patch documentation are tracked directly at the JEANETTE Cybersecurity Framework GitHub Page.
* Syntax Reference Engine: Typing --help, h, or HELP at the main prompt delivers inline configuration arguments, deployment switches, and infrastructure settings on demand.

